### SizeM1BitWidth {#a453599f2782c97d48d8bcedf6f75122d}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype="unsigned llvm::TypeTestResolution::SizeM1BitWidth = 0">
Range of size-1 expressed as a bit width.

For example, if the size is in range &#91;1,256&#93;, this number will be 8. This helps generate the most compact instruction sequences.
